## Project Title
Avarice and Gluttony

## What are you building?
You can either scavenge for resources, combine resources into different ones, check your recipe book, check your compendium of resources and their descriptions, use your creations to your benefit, or sell them in a shop of your very own!

## Why is this a Java 2 project?
I would probably be using lists, stacks, or queues for things like the player's inventory, compendium, and recipe book.

## What is your MVP?
You can scavenge for resources (after choosing to scavenge, you obtain 1 random resource from a large pool, 2 if lucky), combine them (choose 2 items, depending on what they are they become something else), use them (the game tells you what happened), or sell them (you gain money).

## Stretch Goals (optional)
What would you add with extra time?
Various stats showing the benefit your items had towards you when using them, the recipe book containing all combinations you've already seen, and the compendium of all unique resources that have already been found/made. There would also probably be an option to choose to scavenge in different biomes and places, with a curated pool of resources for those places. Also, there would be flavor text showcasing the protagonist's avarice and gluttony.

